The eight forms of marriage are defined in **Chapter 1** of the Yājñavalkya Smṛti, in the *vivāhaprakaraṇam* (Marriage) section, across verses 58–61. The four "approved" forms (Brāhma, Daiva, Ārṣa, Kāya) are in vv. 58–60, and the four "disapproved" forms (Āsura, Gāndharva, Rākṣasa, Paiśāca) are all packed into v. 61.
